This paper deals with the problem of scheduling platoons of autonomous vehicles, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms to minimize delays, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The problem involves scheduling and optimization, which are key topics in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the intersection of traffic, which is a topic in social and information networks (cs.SI).
